.TH "dpsw_set_irq_enable" 9 "dpsw_set_irq_enable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dpsw_set_irq_enable \- Set overall interrupt state.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" dpsw_set_irq_enable
.BI "(struct fsl_mc_io *mc_io "  ","
.BI "u32 cmd_flags "  ","
.BI "u16 token "  ","
.BI "u8 irq_index "  ","
.BI "u8 en "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "mc_io" 12
Pointer to MC portal's I/O object
.IP "cmd_flags" 12
Command flags; one or more of 'MC_CMD_FLAG_'
.IP "token" 12
Token of DPCI object
.IP "irq_index" 12
The interrupt index to configure
.IP "en" 12
Interrupt state - enable = 1, disable = 0
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allows GPP software to control when interrupts are generated.
Each interrupt can have up to 32 causes.  The enable/disable control's the
overall interrupt state. if the interrupt is disabled no causes will cause
an interrupt
.SH "RETURN"
'0' on Success; Error code otherwise.
